news.title: Robust demand for engineering infrastructure from Southeast Asia: Bridging the business & engineering gap via this SME
news.para: Ishan International has been a certified star export house recognized by EEPC for the past 26 years due to its 80% market share in the Southeast Asian market.

news.title: Nine properties in Delhi's Rohini zone attached for property tax default: Official
news.para: Property tax department of the Rohini Zone was pursuing these cases for a long time and had sent many notices under appropriate sections of Delhi Municipal Corporation Act, 1957, in the past.

news.title: Lucknow: Allotees in a fix over 13th floor which does not exist
news.para: In 2015, LDA had proposed to build a multi-storeyed Samajwadi Lohia Enclave in Para and in 2016 allotment was done through a lottery system.

news.title: Haryana shehri vikas pradhikaran to re-auction surrendered plots
news.para: As of now, even in old and popular urban estates like Panchkula, Gurugram, Sonipat, Karnal, Faridabad and Ambala, there are a number of units where allottees had wilfully defaulted after paying token money or some more money at the time of allotment or auction.

news.title: StayVista raises Rs 40 crore in funding led by DSG Consumer Partners
news.para: Cofounder Amit Damani told ET that the startup was valued at Rs 220 crore after the funding round. The startup partners with luxury villa owners and provides them with manpower, operational expertise and marketing through its app and website.

news.title: Gurugram: Build infrastructure for regular power supply to societies, DHBVN tells six builders
news.para: Till the time remedial steps are taken, the discom has asked the department of town and country planning (DTCP) not to issue any approvals such as occupation certificates, completion certificates or licence renewals for these societies.

news.title: YEIDA to launch residential plot scheme today
news.para: People can apply online in the scheme from September 7 to October 7, while the allotment will be done on November 15 through a draw, officials said.

news.title: Registries of five Palam Vihar flats to be revoked, says deputy commissioner
news.para: After the RWA filed a complaint about illegal registration of five flats in violation of the norms, Yadav called a joint meeting of district town planner, revenue and power department officials.

news.title: Restart sand mining through traditional extractors: Goa CM
news.para: Sawant also directed the mines department to put in place a proper online transit pass system for transportation of sand or other minor minerals from neighbouring states.

news.title: Strata forays into Pune market, raises Rs 35 crore for office property in Hinjewadi
news.para: The office has been pre-leased for a period of nine years with a lock-in period of six years. Additionally, the asset is expected to generate a net investor annual internal rate of return (IRR) of 13.10%, the company said.

news.title: Chennai civic body starts separate portal for property tax
news.para: Property owners have also been asked to pay tax due to the Metropolitan Chennai Corporation by September 30 to avoid interest charges, sources said.

news.title: Secunderabad cantonment board fixes fee for mutation of name in property register
news.para: Property owners will now have to pay 2,000 for mutation of name in property tax register and another Rs 350 as publication fee.

news.title: HC refuses to interfere with order granting interim bail to businessman in DHFL case
news.para: Observing that there was no ground to interfere with the order, Justice Sudhir Kumar Jain noted that the documents showed that Nawandar was receiving treatment from a hospital in Mumbai and thus allowed him to travel there for three days with prior intimation to the investigating officer.

news.title: Uttarakhand land law panel submits report, suggests stricter norms
news.para: The panel, headed by former chief secretary Subash Kumar, in its report recommended stricter land laws in Uttarakhand along the lines of neighbouring Himachal Pradesh.

news.title: Canara Bank raises benchmark lending rate by up to 0.15%
news.para: The benchmark one-year MCLR will be 7.75 per cent against the existing rate of 7.65 per cent. The one-year rate is used to fix most consumer loans such as auto, personal and home loans.
